comment_data.body: Render `@note` items as a markdown list because LuaLS doesn't appear to support `@note` items, or at least our hover doc doesn't render them specially. This is easy to change later if our hover doc or LuaLS gains support.

comment_data.body: Currently abusing `md_to_vimdoc` here since we don't have something like `md_to_docstring`, or some other way to format/fit markdown text into the rendered docstring. cc @lewis6991 for sanity check
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -315,6 +327,26 @@ local function render_api_meta(_f, fun, write)
     end
   end
 
+  -- LuaLS doesn't support @note. Render @note items as a markdown list.
+  if fun.notes and #fun.notes > 0 then
+    -- local notes = 'Note:\n'
+    write('--- Note:')
+    for _, note in ipairs(fun.notes) do
+      note = text_utils.md_to_vimdoc(' - ' .. note, 0, 0, 74)
+      for _, l in ipairs(split(vim.trim(norm_text(note)))) do
+        write('--- ' .. l:gsub('\n*$', ''))

comment_data.body:
There's a bit of inconsistency: some has backticks, some does not -- as a result of the mixed use of `/// @see foo` and `/// @see |bar|` in the source file.

Could be out of scope of this PR, but I'd like to note that LuaCATs (https://luals.github.io/wiki/annotations/#see) does not suggest the referenced symbol be quoted; without backticks these can be "hovered" whereas inline code blocks can't.

comment_data.body:
> mixed use of `/// @see foo` and `/// @see |bar|` in the source file.

Which source files? all the `_meta/*` files should consistently use backticks. I didn't find any `|` in _meta files.

> LuaCATs does not suggest the referenced symbol be quoted; without backticks LSPs these can be "hovered"

Definitely worth considering. @lewis6991 what do you think?

 --- Unmaps a buffer-local `mapping` for the given mode.
 ---
+--- @see `nvim_del_keymap()`

comment_data.body:
Sorry it wasn't clear enough; I meant `src/api/*.c` files. e.g.:
- `/// @see |nvim_set_keymap()|` (`api/buffer.c`)
- `/// @see nvim_create_user_command` (`api/command.c`)

In this PR's diff, those who don't have backticks include: `nvim_create_user_command`, `nvim_err_write`, `feedkeys`, `nvim_get_hl_by_name`, `nvim_get_hl_by_id`, `replace_termcodes`, includes `cpoptions`.

comment_data.body:
The use of `|x|` in `src/api/*.c` is intentional for things that have `:help` tags. Those docs get rendered as :help and we want those tags to work in :help.

Hard to automate that without introducing false positives.
